      <tr>
        <td bgcolor="dimgray" valign="top">
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">
        
		<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=1956">
        	
		<font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"><b>SaitTan</a>
        </b></font>

        <br><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1"><small>Decaying Skeleton</small></font>

        <br>
        <br>
        <br><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1"><small>USA</small></font>
        <br><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1"><small>20 Posts</small></font></td>
        <td bgcolor="dimgray" colspan="2" ><img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;07/17/2001&nbsp;:&nbsp; 06:39:14</font>

        
		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=1956"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=1956')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('http://edit.yahoo.com/config/send_webmesg?.target=it_is_me_satan&.src=pg')"><img src="icon_yahoo.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Send SaitTan a Yahoo! Message" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=6006&FORUM_ID=8&CAT_ID=3&Forum_Title=Quest+Hall&Topic_Title=Black+Lace+Sash+quest+in+the+Warrens"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I know most of you probably wouldn't need this item, but it is a great low level waist slot item for those of us that don't have a braided cinch cord or better.  Even Allakhazams didn't have a very good strategy for getting this thing, so I'll post here my findings.</P><P>First of all, the Black Lace Sash is +2int, +2dex, +2agi, AC2, wt. 0.1, all/all, and is dropable and is not Lore.</P><P>It is aquired through Azzar's Dreadful Hat quest (the first part of the quest, there are 2 parts).  Azzar Habbib seems to have had his hat stolen by a large bat, which happens to be the Cave Bat Lord in the Warrens.  The room that the Cave Bat Lord is in is in the very back of the Warrens, past the throne room.  The room contains 4 large bat spawns and a mound in the center of the circular room where the Cave Bat Lord spawns once an hour, provided you take out the bat spawns to make him pop.  At least that was my experience.  The hour time is correct, I timed it on several occassions.  You also don't have to wipe out the various bat spawns to get him to spawn but just once.</P><P>I did this quest as a level 24 Necro and it was extreme cake.  Most everthing in the Warrens conned green to me, although I did find the occasional high green that would attack me on sight.  The Cave Bat Lord conned blue and died very fast to a buffed 24 pet, a Siphon Life or two, and a Shock of Poison thrown in for good measure.  He does flee so be sure to Darkness him.</P><P>Now, here is the part that gives people some confusion.  There are two versions of the Cave Bat Lord.  He can spawn as a freakin' large Werebat looking thing or a huge Kobold from Hell.  According to various posts on Allakhazams, only the large Kobold form drops Azzar's Dreadful Hat.  This is NOT true!  I had a total of 4 Cave Bat Lords spawn before I got my hat, and the one that dropped it was the large Werebat form.  For me he spawned the first 2 times in Werebat form, the next time as a large Kobold, then the final time as a Werebat.</P><P>Another problem that I haven't seen anyone address was the fact that Azzar Habbib despawns.  Upon getting my hat, I invis'd up and broke for the surface (getting attacked by high green Greater Shamans along the way, who can obviously see through Shadows).  I had read that Azzar was in the Observatory overlooking the newbie grounds.  Well, I run up there and only that Bloodpool punk was there.  I figured that Azzar was just not spawned so I waited around, practicing that damned Divination skill while I waited.  It took about 15 minutes before he popped up, in the room that you first enter upon climbing the stairs.</P><P>I handed Azzar the Hat and recieved the following faction:  +Heretic -DeepwaterKnights -GateCallers -Craftkeepers -CrimsonHands.</P><P>I suppose that is about it.  I hope this helps some of you get a rather nice belt.  One thing though, I think you have to be a Cazic-Thule worshipper, or probably have amazing faction with the Heretics, to do this quest, as the Hat you get off the Cave Bat Lord has "Cazic-Thule" as part of it's attributes.</P><P>There is a second part to the hat quest involving the Might Bear Paw that can be found a little past the Cave Bat Lord room.  I took him out about 4 times while waiting on the CBL to spawn, he was a little harder and conned even to me.  The quest piece needed from him is the Bear Paw Pelt.</P><P><BR>Sait Tan<BR>24 Erudite Necromancer<BR>Broken Blades, Prexus</font></td>
      </tr>

